rComments: Dr. Brusso is passionate about the material which is conveyed in her lecturing style. She tries her best to assist students' needs; accessible in office hours, in class, after class and responds to emails quickly. The material is cumulative and you need to keep up with it; it only gets harder. Her slides have everything you need in them.

Dr. Brusso is an amazing professor. She is really passionate about the topic of advanced materials research, which is conveyed throughout the class lectures. She understands that students may excel in areas other than testing, so she evaluates mainly on presentations, and class discussions. Midterms cannot be avoided, though the Qs are very fair.

Brusso is actually a very kind person and accessible outside of class hours. She is very clear on what type of questions she'll ask, and she will point them out in the lecture, so it's all fair game. She talks quickly, but that's because there is a lot of content to go through in the class. Her lecture slides outline everything you need to know.

One of the worst profs I've had. She's nice and all, but her teaching sucks. She teaches concepts and theories in class, and the exams are problem-based. She makes a lot of mistakes during class and this got a lot of students confused. the material itself isn't bad, but don't solely rely on her for ur understanding. Youtube helped me barely pass.

Avoid this prof at all cost! It's very unfortunate that she's the only prof for this mandatory course. uOttawa really needs to give this job to someone else if they're going to keep it a 1-person taught course. Also, she teaches 95% theory & the exams are 100% problems. Lastly, she gets frustrated when people don't answer her questions in class...

Probably the worst professor I've had during my time at university. She loves talking about how difficult and important the material is in real life, but when it comes to actually teaching she reverts to reading the slides, word-for-word, and not being able to express her point. This course is only hard, since she cannot teach to save her life!

The material is easy and she does examples in class which are helpful. Refuses to post solutions to her problem sets and some problem sets only have 3 questions which is useless. She's very condescending when you try and ask her questions and is horrible at explaining concepts cuz she stutters and isn't able to make a coherent sentence.

She clearly prefers her lab to lecturing, but in office hours, she is extremely helpful. The lectures themselves aren't bad, she just has lots of slides (sometimes up to 60 slides per lecture). Exams are mostly fair, but require lots of studying. She's a very nice professor, and she knows her stuff. Would take again.

This class isn't as bad as some people make it out to be, though I have a suspension she may have dumb-ed it down this year based on past averages. The midterms and final are all application which she let's you know on the first day. Her slides are a little long but are fairly clear. Overall, not a horrible course but it wasn't the best either.

2311: Exams do not have many surprises. What is expected is clear and marking is fair. Not many practice problems are provided but the slides are good. Pretty goodengaging lecturer. 2128: No textbook or practice problems. Excellent slides. Very fair (and easy) exams. Great teaching style w lots of discussion. Both courses are recomended

As long as you go to class and listen, you'll be fine. Her notes are relatively good, as long as you study from them you're good. Prof tries too hard to get the class to participate. There's little homework provided, but the tests itself are not too difficult.

Good prof, there was no doubt about what would or wouldn't be fair game for the final. Midterms were pretty easy if you attended class. Got pretty upset whenever people didn't answer her questions, but it was a good class.

Class understanding is low, this is reflective in average grades. Teaching style is terrible, with fill in the blank notes. Notes alone are very poor powerpoints, with very little useful homework given. Only teaches theory, no solutions ever posted. Avoid prof.
awful.

AWFUL LECTURE STYLE. She teaches it on all slides as if its a theory class yet the exams are ALL problems. It's a "teach yourself "kind of class because she does not provide you with the skills or knowledge to succeed in her class! Best of luck, and use YouTube!
Really smart and tries to make the course understandable. Structure is hard though so expect a heavy workload if you want to keep up

Horrible lecture style. May know her stuff but oversimplifies in class and says do more problems instead of expanding her material. Leaves blanks in slides, asks questions that don't lead to discussion or understanding checks. Never prompt, almost got a pepper until I wore my glasses
Great Prof! She knows her stuff and is always willing to help if you express it. Don't be a smart ass with her and you won't get smart ass answers

Very smart. Tried very hard to simplify concepts, and evidently made it much more difficult to understand. Lack of practice questions on difficult concepts (GO) really hurt understanding. Awful textbook in combination with a lack of information available online made this class a REAL struggle.
The worst prof for structures and bonding where no one knows what she's talking about in class. Clarity in the class is at a -5.
She is very good and helpful
awesome
